            </li>

            <li>
                <i class="fa-solid fa-recycle"></i>
                <p><strong>Sustainability</strong> — Prioritizing resource‑efficient, environmentally conscious methods.</p>
            </li>

            <li>
                <i class="fa-solid fa-book-open"></i>
                <p><strong>Education</strong> — Creating opportunities for learning, research, and outreach.</p>
            </li>

            <li>
                <i class="fa-solid fa-scale-balanced"></i>
                <p><strong>Equity</strong> — Imagining systems where everyone has access to healthy food.</p>
            </li>

            <li>
                <i class="fa-solid fa-lightbulb"></i>
                <p><strong>Innovation</strong> — Using research to refine and improve aquaponics models.</p>
            </li>

        </ul>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- ========================= -->
<!-- NONPROFIT STATUS (pale blue) -->
<!-- ========================= -->
<section class="pale-blue">
    <div class="section-inner">
        <h2>Nonprofit Status (Conceptual)</h2>
        <p>
            Ripple is presented as a hypothetical nonprofit for the purposes of this honors 
            project. While the website references nonprofit structures such as 
            <strong>501(c)(3)</strong> status, these elements are part of the academic 
            demonstration and are not legally established.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>
